    <div class="container">
        <header id="header">
            <h1 style="text-align: center;"><i class="fas fa-film"></i> Ramoji Film City</h1>
            <p>The World's Largest Film Studio Complex</p>
            <div class="hyderabad-badge">
                <i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Hayathnagar, Hyderabad, Telangana, India
            </div>
        </header>

        <div class="main-image-container">
            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1612872087720-bb876e2e1d31?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1350&q=80"
                alt="Ramoji Film City" class="main-image">
            <div class="image-overlay">
                <h2>"A World of Cinematic Wonders"</h2>
                <p>Experience the magic of filmmaking in Asia's largest film studio</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <section class="description" id="description">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-history"></i> About Ramoji Film City</h2>
            <p>Ramoji Film City, located in Hyderabad, is the world's largest film studio complex, sprawling over 1,666 acres. Certified by Guinness World Records, it is a hub for filmmaking, tourism, and entertainment, attracting visitors with its cinematic sets, adventure activities, and vibrant attractions.</p>

            <div class="historical-fact">
                Established in 1996 by Ramoji Rao, this iconic destination has been the filming location for over 2,000 Indian films, including blockbusters like "Baahubali."
            </div>

            <p>From guided studio tours to thrilling adventure zones, Ramoji Film City offers a unique blend of education and entertainment. Its beautifully landscaped gardens, interactive exhibits, and live shows make it a perfect destination for families, film enthusiasts, and adventure seekers.</p>

            <h3 style="margin-top: 20px; color: var(--hyderabad-blue);"><i class="fas fa-star"></i> Key Features</h3>
            <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-top: 10px;">
                <li>Guided studio tours showcasing filmmaking</li>
                <li>Adventure activities at Sahas Adventure Land</li>
                <li>Iconic film sets like the Baahubali kingdom</li>
                <li>Water rides and live entertainment shows</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <div class="nearby-section">
            <section class="restaurants" id="restaurants">
                <h2 class="section-title"><i class="fas fa-utensils"></i> Budget-Friendly Restaurants</h2>

                <div class="restaurant">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1631515243349-e0cb75fb8d3a?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80"
                            alt="Alankrita Restaurant" class="restaurant-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-drumstick-bite"></i> Alankrita Restaurant <span class="hyderabadi-badge">Vegetarian</span></h3>
                    <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Ramoji Film City (~0.5 km)</p>
                    <p class="timings"><i class="far fa-clock"></i> 8:00 AM - 10:00 PM (Daily)</p>
                    <div class="must-try">
                        <span>Must Try:</span> Masala Dosa, Paneer Tikka, Lassi
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="restaurant">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1600891964599-f61ba0e24092?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80"
                            alt="Ganga Jamuna Restaurant" class="restaurant-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-pepper-hot"></i> Ganga Jamuna Restaurant</h3>
                    <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Ramoji Film City (~0.5 km)</p>
                    <p class="timings"><i class="far fa-clock"></i> 11:00 AM - 10:00 PM (Daily)</p>
                    <div class="must-try">
                        <span>Must Try:</span> Hyderabadi Biryani, Chicken 65, Andhra Thali
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="restaurant">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1598515214211-89d3c73ae83b?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80"
                            alt="Chanakya Restaurant" class="restaurant-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-bread-slice"></i> Chanakya Restaurant</h3>
                    <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Hayathnagar (~2 km)</p>
                    <p class="timings"><i class="far fa-clock"></i> 7:00 AM - 9:00 PM (Daily)</p>
                    <div class="must-try">
                        <span>Must Try:</span> South Indian Breakfast, Veg Thali, Filter Coffee
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="restaurant">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1610057099431-0567e7f15bcb?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80"
                            alt="Sai Krishna Dhaba" class="restaurant-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-utensils"></i> Sai Krishna Dhaba</h3>
                    <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Hayathnagar (~3 km)</p>
                    <p class="timings"><i class="far fa-clock"></i> 10:00 AM - 11:00 PM (Daily)</p>
                    <div class="must-try">
                        <span>Must Try:</span> Paneer Butter Masala, Dal Makhani, Naan
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="restaurant">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1606491956689-2ea866880c84?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80"
                            alt="Srinidhi Udupi" class="restaurant-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-tint"></i> Srinidhi Udupi</h3>
                    <p><i class="fas fa-map-marker-alt"></i> Hayathnagar (~4 km)</p>
                    <p class="timings"><i class="far fa-clock"></i> 7:00 AM - 10:00 PM (Daily)</p>
                    <div class="must-try">
                        <span>Must Try:</span> Rava Idli, Vada, Coconut Chutney
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="famous-places" id="attractions">
                <h2 class="section-title"><i class="fas fa-map-marked-alt"></i> Attractions at Ramoji Film City</h2>

                <div class="place">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1578985545068-404c9460f6b6?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80"
                            alt="Studio Tour" class="place-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-camera"></i> Studio Tour</h3>
                    <div class="distance"><i class="fas fa-walking"></i> On-site at Ramoji Film City</div>
                    <p>Explore the behind-the-scenes magic of filmmaking with guided tours through various sets and studios.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="place">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1593697821352-b158718609b Rui?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80"
                            alt="Bahubali Set" class="place-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-crown"></i> Bahubali Set</h3>
                    <div class="distance"><i class="fas fa-walking"></i> On-site at Ramoji Film City</div>
                    <p>Experience the grandeur of the Mahishmati kingdom from the epic film "Baahubali" with its majestic courtyards and thrones.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="place">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1597072689227-8882273e8e8a?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80"
                            alt="Wings – The Bird Park" class="place-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-dove"></i> Wings – The Bird Park</h3>
                    <div class="distance"><i class="fas fa-walking"></i> On-site at Ramoji Film City</div>
                    <p>Discover a serene sanctuary filled with exotic birds, vibrant colors, and melodious songs amidst lush greenery.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="place">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1600585154340-be6161a56a0c?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80"
                            alt="Sahas Adventure Land" class="place-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-running"></i> Sahas Adventure Land</h3>
                    <div class="distance"><i class="fas fa-walking"></i> On-site at Ramoji Film City</div>
                    <p>Engage in thrilling adventure activities like bungee ejection, zip lining, zorbing, and more in Asia’s largest adventure land.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="place">
                    <div class="image-container">
                        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1593697821352-b158718609b3?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80"
                            alt="Water World" class="place-image">
                    </div>
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-water"></i> Water World</h3>
                    <div class="distance"><i class="fas fa-walking"></i> On-site at Ramoji Film City</div>
                    <p>Relax and have fun with water rides, wave pools, and artificial beaches in this aquatic amusement park.</p>
                </div>
